HEADWORD: Ophiomancy
<hw>O"phi*o*man`cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'o`fis</grk> a serpent + <ets>-mancy</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>ophiomantie</ets>.]</ety> <def>Divination by serpents, as by their
manner of eating, or by their coils.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

